+The Gospel of John opens: *En archē ēn ho Logos* — "In the beginning was the Word/Logos." The identification of the Logos with the divine creative principle, and then with the person of Jesus, is a specific theological move. But the philosophical concept the author is drawing on is the Stoic one: there is a rational structure underlying reality, and contact with that structure is the deepest form of knowledge.
